note over browser:
user inputs new content to the form and clicking save button
end note

note over browser:
'onsubmit' handler gets executed: we prevent the default behavior of the
form and send XMLHttpRequest request instead.
also we push a new note into the notes list and rerender the notes list
end note

browser->server: HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa

note over server:
Backend creates a new note object in memory and pushes it into the
notes list.
Content of the new note is based on the req.body
end note

server-->browser: HTTP STATUS 201 - { message: "note created" }

note over browser:
Basically in this case server just confirms that the operation was 
successfull
end note